4. SIGNAL VS NOISE ANALYSIS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

What adds real value (keep):

  README.md — the actual deliverable of this entire system. Well-structured,
  visually polished, and informative.

  metrics/overview.svg, metrics/github-stats.svg, metrics/top-languages.svg,
  metrics/contributions.svg — the four-panel layout is the right model. Each
  file has a clear, focused purpose.

  branding/header.svg, branding/logo.svg — custom visual identity that
  differentiates the profile from default GitHub profiles.

  docs/secrets.md, docs/architecture.md, docs/workflows.md — documentation
  that captures intent and reduces onboarding friction. High value, recently
  added.

  .github/dependabot.yml — signal that dependency management is taken
  seriously, even if it is not yet fully configured.

  .prettierrc, .markdownlint.json, .editorconfig — consistent style
  configuration. Valuable tooling.

  lint.yml, health.yml — enforcing quality in CI is the right instinct.

  CONTRIBUTING.md — exists and adds credibility to the repository as an
  engineered project rather than a casual profile page.

What is low-value or distracting (remove or reduce):

  64 profile-summary-card theme directories. Only one theme is used in
  the README at any time. Consider limiting output to one or two selected
  themes, or moving all card output to a branch that does not appear in the
  default view.

  github-metrics.svg at the repository root. Superseded by the four-panel
  layout. Its continued presence in the README alongside the panel images
  creates visual redundancy.

  metrics.plugin.16personalities.svg. Orphaned; no workflow generates it in
  a documented way; not referenced anywhere. Should be deleted.

  resume.pdf at the root. Belongs under assets/ or branding/ if it must
  be committed at all. A linked URL to a hosted version (e.g., a GitHub
  release asset) is cleaner than a versioned binary in the repo root.

  audits/metrics-diagnostics.md, audits/metrics-selfhost-diagnostics.md,
  audits/readme-update-diagnostics.md. Informal run notes that add noise
  to the audits/ directory. If retained, move to a subdirectory (audits/logs/)
  or exclude from version control entirely.

  assets/emojis/.gitkeep. The directory has a real file; remove the placeholder.

  docs/.gitkeep. Same: docs/ has real content now.

  The [legacy] step in metrics.yml that regenerates github-metrics.svg.
  Eliminating this step removes an entire lowlighter/metrics invocation,
  reduces API calls, and simplifies the workflow by 20%.


